 alternative transportation options and incentives in a planned effort to meet the gup peak hour trip limit these efforts were developed and coordinated through the parking & transportation services p&ts department the commute club was created to give new and existing alternative transportation users a sense of community and identity thereby increasing both awareness of and participation in alternative transportation programs as well as maintaining member loyalty this program has grown from 3706 members during the 2002 academic year to 6755 in the 2007 academic year an 82 percent increase learn more about current initiatives in transportation the parking & transportation services website has details on all programs as well as current promotions printer friendly version printer friendly version stanford university all rights reserved stanford ca 94305 drupal site designed and developed by wired moon in partnership with lbre
